com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api
Interface GenericTypeArgument

All Superinterfaces:
JSOM
public interface GenericTypeArgument
extends JSOM

This JSOM type represents a generic type argument.

There are four variants of how generic type argument can be stated:

  1. <AnyType>
  2. <?>
  3. <? extends AnyType>
  4. <? super AnyType>
This class supports the representation of all these variants.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

Method Detail

getType

Type getType()
Returns the type stated by the generic type argument.

For the generic type variant Variant.NOT_WILDCARDED the result of the method is the generic type itself but for the variants Variant.WILDCARDED_EXTENDS_BOUND and Variant.WILDCARDED_SUPER_BOUND the returned type corresponds to the bound type (i.e. the type following the extends or super keyword).

Returns:
The type stated by the generic type argument or null if this represents a Variant.WILDCARDED_NOT_BOUND generic type argument.

getVariant

GenericTypeArgument.Variant getVariant()
Returns the variant of the generic type argument represented by this.

Returns:
One of the GenericTypeArgument.Variant.??? constants.
